    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">This tab is</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farms_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Water Balance Subregions</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading2_atoc_" translate="true">Crop on-farm efficiency (OFE)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The crop on-farm efficiency is a number between 0 and 1 that indicates the efficiency with which a farm uses water for a particular crop. For example, if 10% of the water diverted from a stream for irrigation evaporated before being applied as irrigation, the crop on-farm efficiency would be 0.9. Separate values must be specified for each crop. The efficiencies can vary with time.</text></para>
